10 United States Census|2010]]\n|population_footnotes     =<ref name=\"FactFinder\">{{cite web|title=American FactFinder|url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/nav/jsf/pages/index.xhtml|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref>\n|population_total         = 208453\n|population_rank          = US: [[List of United States cities by population|88th]]\n|population_metro         = 4,737,270 (US: [[List of Metropolitan Statistical Areas|11th]])\n|population_density_km2   = 1407.88\n|population_density_sq_mi = 3646.39\n|pop_est_as_of            = 2018\n|population_est           = 248279\n|pop_est_footnotes        =<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\"/>\n|timezone                 = [[Mountain Standard Time Zone|MST]] (no [[Daylight savings time|DST]])\n|utc_offset               = -7\n|coordinates              = {{coord|33|21|10|N|111|47|20|W|region:US-AZ|display=inline,title}}<ref name=gnis/>\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]s\n|postal_code              = 85233, 85234, 85295-85298\n|area_code                = [[Area code 480|480]]\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = {{FIPS|04|27400}}\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] ID(s) = {{GNIS4|5032}}<ref name=gnis/>\n|website                  = {{URL|www.gilbertaz.gov}}\n|footnotes                = \n|area_footnotes =<ref name=\"CenPopGazetteer2016\">{{cite web|title=2018 U.S. Gazetteer Files|url=https://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/2018_Gazetteer/2018_gaz_place_04.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=July 1, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Gilbert''' is a town in [[Maricopa County, Arizona|Maricopa County]], Arizona, United States, located southeast of [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], within the [[Phoenix metropolitan area]]. Once known as the \"Hay Shipping Capital of the World\",<ref>[http://www.usacitiesonline.com/azcountygilbert.htm Gilbert Profile]</ref> It is the sixth-largest municipality in Arizona, and the fifth-largest in the Metropolitan Phoenix Area.\n\nGilbert encompasses {{convert|76|sqmi|km2|0}} and has made a rapid transformation from an agriculture-based community to an economically diverse suburban center located in the southeast valley of the Greater Phoenix area. In the last three decades, Gilbert has grown at an extremely high rate, increasing in population from 5,717 in 1980 to 208,453 as of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]]. The town grew at an average annual growth rate of nearly 13% during this 30-year period. In 2018, the town's population was estimated to be at 248,279.\n\n==History==\nGilbert owes its beginnings to William \"Bobby\" Gilbert, who provided land to the Arizona Eastern Railway in 1902 to construct a rail line between Phoenix and Florence, Arizona. Ayer's Grocery Store, the first store in Gilbert, opened in 1910 and became the location of the first post office in 1912. The location of the town post office moved several times before settling on the east side of Gilbert Road in downtown, where it still stands today.  In 1912, many Mormons who had fled the [[Mormon colonies in Mexico]] due to the actions of the forces of [[Pancho Villa]] settled in Gilbert. By 1915, they began holding church meetings at the Gilbert Elementary School. In 1918, they were organized into the Gilbert Ward.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thechurchnews.com/archive/2010-11-19/gilbert-arizona-communitys-roots-date-to-1920-36358 |title=Gilbert Arizona Community's roots date to 1920|newspaper=[[Church News]] |date=November 19, 2010 |accessdate=September 4, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIncorporated in July 1920, Gilbert was primarily a farming community fueled by the rail line and construction of the Roosevelt Dam and the Eastern and Consolidated Canals. It remained an agricultural town for many years and was known as the \"Hay Capital of the World\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ci.gilbert.az.us/busdev/profile/history.cfm |title=Gilbert History |publisher=Ci.gilbert.az.us |accessdate=September 4, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100417155420/http://www.ci.gilbert.az.us/busdev/profile/history.cfm |archivedate=April 17, 2010  }}</ref> from 1911 until the late 1920s.\n\nIn 2019, the town featured highly on three national surveys, related to safety, livability and family life; it was named the fourth-safest (of 182 communities), twelfth-most livable town, and seventh-best place to raise a family in the United States.<ref name=\"Steinbach2019\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/43390829/gilbert_ranks_highest_on_safety/|title=Gilbert ranks highest on safety, livability|last=Steinbach|first=Alison|date=December 26, 2019|work=Arizona Business Gazette|access-date=|url-status=live|publisher=Gannett|agency=USA Today Network|issue=52|location=Phoenix, Arizona|volume=139|page=4|via=Newspapers.com}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nGilbert is located in the southeast portion of the [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]] metropolitan area. It is south of [[Mesa, Arizona|Mesa]] and northeast of [[Chandler, Arizona|Chandler]].<ref>''Chandler, AZ,'' 7.5 Minute Topographic Quadrangle, USGS, 1952 (1982 rev.)</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], in the 2000 Census, the town had an estimated area of {{convert|40|sqmi|km2|0}}. As of 2009, and due to annexations the current Municipal Planning Area of Gilbert has a total area of {{convert|76.0|sqmi|km2|0}}, of which {{convert|75.76|sqmi|km2|1}} is land and {{convert|0.24|sqmi|km2|1}} is water.\n\n===Climate===\nGilbert has a tropical and subtropical, hot desert type of climate ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]] BWh) with dry and hot summers, and mild to warm winters, with little rainfall.\n\n<div style=\"width:70%\">\n{{Weather box|location = Gilbert, Arizona\n|single line = Y\n|Jan record high F =  89\n|Feb record high F =  95\n|Mar record high F =  99\n|Apr record high F = 106\n|May record high F = 118\n|Jun record high F = 116\n|Jul record high F = 119\n|Aug record high F = 115\n|Sep record high F = 113\n|Oct record high F = 107\n|Nov record high F =  97\n|Dec record high F =  86\n|Jan high F =  67\n|Feb high F =  71\n|Mar high F =  77\n|Apr high F =  85\n|May high F =  94\n|Jun high F = 104\n|Jul high F = 106\n|Aug high F = 104\n|Sep high F =  99\n|Oct high F =  89\n|Nov high F =  75\n|Dec high F =  67\n\n|Jan low F = 41\n|Feb low F = 45\n|Mar low F = 49\n|Apr low F = 54\n|May low F = 61\n|Jun low F = 70\n|Jul low F = 77\n|Aug low F = 76\n|Sep low F = 70\n|Oct low F = 59\n|Nov low F = 47\n|Dec low F = 40\n\n|Jan record low F = 15\n|Feb record low F = 19\n|Mar record low F = 24\n|Apr record low F = 30\n|May record low F = 37\n|Jun record low F = 43\n|Jul record low F = 54\n|Aug record low F = 51\n|Sep record low F = 40\n|Oct record low F = 30\n|Nov record low F = 22\n|Dec record low F = 17\n|Jan precipitation inch = 1.01\n|Feb precipitation inch = 1.03\n|Mar precipitation inch = 1.19\n|Apr precipitation inch = 0.33\n|May precipitation inch = 0.13\n|Jun precipitation inch = 0.04\n|Jul precipitation inch = 0.89\n|Aug precipitation inch = 1.14\n|Sep precipitation inch = 0.89\n|Oct precipitation inch = 0.81\n|Nov precipitation inch = 0.77\n|Dec precipitation inch = 0.98\n\n|source 1 = The Weather Channel<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.weather.com/outlook/health/fitness/wxclimatology/monthly/graph/USAZ0082 | title = Average Weather for Gilbert, AZ \u2013 Temperature and Precipitation | publisher = Weather.com | accessdate = August 24, 2017}}</ref>}}\n\n{|style=\"width:100%;text-align:center;line-height:1.2em;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible\"\n|-\n!Colspan=14|Climate data for Gilbert\n|-\n!Month\n!Jan\n!Feb\n!Mar\n!Apr\n!May\n!Jun\n!Jul\n!Aug\n!Sep\n!Oct\n!Nov\n!Dec\n!style=\"border-left-width:medium\"|Year\n|-\n!Mean daily daylight hours\n|style=\"background:#F0F011;color:#000000;\"|10.0\n|style=\"background:#F7F722;co