|ShortSummary= All of the regular characters are seen living different lives. Booth and Brennan are married and own a nightclub called \"The Lab\", but when a body is found at the club, Detectives Cam Saroyan and Jared Booth are called to investigate. However, not everything is as it seems. For example, Caroline Julian, normally a federal prosecutor, is a defense lawyer, and Sweets is the frontman of the band [[Gormogon (Bones)|Gormogon]], who was a cannibalistic serial killer. It is subsequently revealed that Booth has been in a coma for several days due to his tumor operation and that the life he saw was possibly only a dream or a hallucination. It is also revealed that Brennan had been writing at his side, possibly narrating her story out loud as she wrote it, causing Booth to hallucinate what he did. She ends up deleting her work. The episode ends with Booth awakening from his coma without any memory of who Brennan is.\n |WrittenBy=Hart Hanson\n |DirectedBy=Ian Toynton\n |Viewers=8.70<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2009/05/15/ratings-abc-greys-anatomy-win-finale-thursday-but-declines-continue/18685/ |title=Ratings: ABC, Grey's Anatomy Win \"Finale Thursday\"; But Declines Continue |work=TV by the Numbers |first=Bill |last=Gorman |date=May 15, 2009 |accessdate=November 10, 2012}}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2009|5|14}}\n |ProdCode=4AKY20\n |LineColor=26466D\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n== DVD and Blu-ray release ==\nThe fourth season of ''Bones'' was released on DVD (subtitled \"Body Bag Edition\") in region 1 on October 6, 2009,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B001L1S1OY/ |title=Bones: Season Four (Body Bag Edition) |work=Amazon.com |accessdate=March 24, 2010}}</ref> in region 2 on October 26, 2009<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B001UE8IZE/ |title=Bones - Season 4 - Complete |work=Amazon.co.uk |accessdate=March 24, 2010}}</ref> and in region 4 on October 27, 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ezydvd.com.au/item.zml/807906 |title=Bones (2005) - Season 4: Body Bag Edition (7 Disc Set) |work=EzyDVD.com.au |accessdate=March 24, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100312055645/http://www.ezydvd.com.au/item.zml/807906# |archive-date=March 12, 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> This was the first season to be released on Blu-ray, and was only released in region A alongside the region 1 DVD release. The region 1 DVD set only includes 22 episodes of season four, as the first four episodes of the season were made available as bonus episodes on the season three DVD set. While the Blu-ray release, and the region 2 and 4 versions include all 26 episodes of the season. Special features include two featurettes\u2014\"Androgyny: Playing Haru Tanaka\" and \"Squints in Training\"; three extended episodes\u2014\"The Perfect Pieces in the Purple Pond\", \"The Doctor in the Den\" and \"The Girl in the Mask\". Also included are deleted scenes and a gag reel.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Bones-Season-4-Press-Release/12523 |title=Bones - Official Season 4 Press Release |work=TVShowsOnDVD.com |accessdate=April 4, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100330040217/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Bones-Season-4-Press-Release/12523 |archivedate=March 30, 2010 }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n{{refbegin}}\n'''General references''' <!-- These references will apply to most, if not all, episodes -->\n* {{Cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/bones/episodes-season-4/192241|title=Bones Season 4 episodes|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=April 4, 2010}}\n* {{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/bones/listings/|title=Shows A\u2013Z \u2013 bones on fox|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|accessdate=April 4, 2010}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official website|http://www.fox.com/bones/}}\n* {{Imdb episodes|0460627|Bones}}\n* {{Tv.com episodes|bones|33332|Bones|4}}\n\n{{Bones}}\n\n[[Category:2008 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:2009 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:Bones (TV series)|Season 04]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Infobox television season\n |season_number = 4\n |image = [[File:Bones-s4-dvd.jpg]]\n |caption = Season 4 DVD cover art\n |bgcolour = #26466D\n |country = United States\n |network = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n |first_aired = {{Start date|2008|9|3}}\n |last_aired = {{End date|2009|5|14}}\n |num_episodes = 26\n |episode_list = List of Bones episodes\n}}\nThe fourth season of the American television series ''[[Bones (TV series)|Bones]]'' premiered on September 3, 2008, with a two-hour episode and concluded on May 14, 2009, on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]. The show changed time slots again, airing on Wednesdays at 8:00 pm ET before moving to Thursdays at 8:00 pm ET in 2009. The season consisted of 26 episodes and averaged 10.8 million viewers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abcmedianet.com/web/dnr/dispDNR.aspx?id=052709_07 |title=Season Rankings (Through 5/24)|work=ABC Medianet |date=May 27, 2009 |accessdate=April 4, 2010}}</ref>\n\n== Cast and characters ==\n{{See also|List of Bones characters}}\n\n=== Main cast ===\n*[[Emily Deschanel]] as [[Temperance \"Bones\" Brennan|Dr. Temperance \"Bones\" Brennan]], a [[forensic anthropologist]]\n*[[David Boreanaz]] as FBI Special Agent [[Seeley Booth]], a the official FBI liaison with the Jeffersonian\n*[[Michaela Conlin]] as [[Angela Montenegro]], a [[forensic artist]]\n*[[T. J. Thyne]] as [[Jack Hodgins (Bones)|Dr. Jack Hodgins]], an [[entomologist]]\n*[[Tamara Taylor]] as [[Camille Saroyan|Dr. Camille Saroyan]], a [[forensic pathologist]] and the head of the forensic division\n*[[John Francis Daley]] as [[Lance Sweets|Dr. Lance Sweets]], an FBI [[psychologist]] who studies the relationship between Dr. Brennan and Agent Booth\n\n=== Recurring cast ===\n*[[David Greenman]] as [[List of Bones characters#Marcus Geier|Marcus Geier]], a forensic technician\n*[[Patricia Belcher]] as [[List of Bones characters#Caroline Julian|Caroline Julian]], a prosecutor\n*[[Brendan Fehr]] as [[List of Bones characters#Jared Booth|Jared Booth]], Booth's brother\n*[[Marisa Coughlan]] as FBI Agent [[List of Bones characters#Payton Perotta|Payton Perotta]]\n*[[Nichole Hiltz]] as Roxie Lyon, Angela\u2019s girlfriend\n*[[Tuppence Middleton]] as Vera Waterhouse\n*[[Eric Millegan]] as Dr. [[Zack Addy]]\n*[[Ryan O'Neal]] as [[List of Bones characters#Matthew Brennan / Max Keenan|Max Keenan]], Brennan's father\n*[[Ty Panitz]] as [[List of Bones characters#Parker Booth|Parker Booth]], Booth's son\n*[[Stephen Fry]] as Dr. [[List of Bones characters#Gordon Wyatt|Gordon Wyatt]], Booth's former psychiatrist\n*[[Billy Gibbons]] as Angela's father\n*[[Deirdre Lovejoy]] as [[List of Bones characters#The Grave Digger|Heather Taffet]]\n\n;Interns\n*[[Eugene Byrd]] as Dr. [[List of Bones characters#Clark Edison|Clark Edison]]\n*[[Ryan Cartwright]] as [[List of Bones characters#Vincent Nigel-Murray|Vincent Nigel-Murray]]\n*[[Michael Grant Terry]] as [[List of Bones characters#Wendell Bray|Wendell Bray]]\n*[[Carla Gallo]] as [[List of Bones characters#Daisy Wick|Daisy Wick]]\n*[[Joel David Moore]] as [[List of Bones characters#Colin Fisher|Colin Fisher]]\n*[[Pej Vahdat]] as [[List of Bones characters#Arastoo Vaziri|Arastoo Vaziri]]\n*[[Michael Badalucco]] as Scott Starret\n\n== Episodes ==\nThe season premieres with its first two-part episode, \"Yanks in the U.K.\" which was filmed on-location in the [[United Kingdom]]. Due to the season's extended episode count of 26 and multiple pre-emptions, Fox aired seven episodes throughout the month of April 2009, with new episodes airing on Monday and Wednesday, along with its regular timeslot of Thursday.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2009/04/02/bones-to-visit-monday-wednesday-nights-in-april-30918/8024/ |title=Bones to Visit Monday, Wednesday Nights in April |work=The Futon Critic |date=April 2, 2009 |accessdate=November 10, 2012}}</ref> This season sees the return of [[The Grave Digger (Bones)|The Grave Digger]], who was last seen in the second season. This time, The Grave Digger captures Booth. After Booth is rescued, the team discovers the true identity of The Grave Digger.\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table\n|background  = #26466D\n|overall     = 6\n|season      = 6\n|title       = 23\n|director    = 14\n|writer      = 19\n|airdate     = 16\n|prodcode    = 6\n|viewers     = 10\n|country     = US\n|episodes    = \n{{Episode list/sublist|Bones (season 4)\n |MainList=List of Bones episodes\n |EpisodeNumber=59<hr />60\n |EpisodeNumber2=1<hr />2\n |Title=Yanks in the U.K.\n |ShortSummary=This two-hour season premiere, begins when Booth and Brennan are at [[Oxford University]] in [[Oxford]], [[England]] for a conference. They are then called to [[London]] to help solve a case in collaboration with a pair of British investigators from [[Scotland Yard]]. Meanwhile, Angela's estranged husband, Grayson Barasa, is finally found, but he refuses to sign the divorce papers, much to the dismay of Hodgins and Angela.<hr />When one of the British investigators is murdered, Booth and Brennan become more determined to help solve the murder. Meanwhile, Angela and Hodgins continue to have relationship problems regarding their marriage.\n |WrittenBy=[[Hart Hanson]] & Karine Rosenthal<hr />Stephen Nathan & [[Scott A. Williams|Scott Williams]]\n |DirectedBy=[[Ian Toynton]]\n |Viewers=9.17<ref name=\"s4 premiere ratings\">{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2008/09/04/ratings-wednesday-september-3-bones-opens-strong-top-model-weak/4917/ |title=Ratings Wednesday, September 3: Bones Opens Strong, Top Model Weak |work=TV by the Numbers |first=Bill |last=Gorman |date=September 4, 2008 |accessdate=November 10, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130108093155/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2008/09/04/ratings-wednesday-september-3-bones-